  articleH2Text=" In a city like Berlin, analogue photobooths are part of the street's pulse, documenting nights out, friendships, and fleeting moments."
/>

<ArticleBanner bannerImage={HSbanner} imageAltText="booth 1" />

<ArticleH3 articleH3Text="these little capsules lay scattered across the city, imprinting us in their raw touch" />

<ArticleParagraph
  articlePText={`In Berlin, analogue photobooths aren't just machines—they're part of the city's street culture. Scattered across Kreuzberg and Friedrichshain, these booths catch friendships, nights out, and random moments in grainy black-and-white strips you can hold in your hand. The wait, the flash, the chemical smell—it's all part of the ritual.`}
/>

<ArticleParagraph
  articlePText={`Today, the walls are layered with stories told in paint and paste-ups, 
  mixing political commentary and sharp urban wit. The alley and surrounding buildings are
  not polished or curated for visitors - they're messy, powerful, and beautifully real. 
    If you want a glimpse of Berlin that doesn't come with a price tag or glossy filter, 
  this is where you'll find it.`}
/>

